TY  - JOUR
TI  - Technology Diffusion, Substitution, and X-Efficiency
AU  - Shen, T. Y.
AB  - [This paper examines the possible explanations for the changes in output, capital, and labor input of a sample of manufacturing plants over a number of years. Apart from the scale of operation, these changes could be attributed to three causes: technology diffusion, substitution, and improvements in X-efficiency. The empirical findings indicate that a diffusion model modified to incorporate X-efficiency improvements provides the best explanation. This suggests the need for a new approach to the specification of production functions.]
C1  - Full publication date: Mar., 1973
DB  - JSTOR
DO  - 10.2307/1913489
EP  - 284
IS  - 2
